  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 10 high, 7 medium, 22 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 7 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and RVR limitations  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS) and Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR). Network hotspots: Cristiano Ronaldo (FNC/LPMA), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 3 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, RVR limitations and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and 9 others.",
